  "prompt": "Which IT direct vendor companies sponsors H1B for students who went to school in USA and have experience?",
  "response": "Several direct vendor companies in the IT industry sponsor H-1B visas for international students who have studied in the U.S. and have relevant experience. These companies often look for highly skilled tech professionals and can navigate the H-1B visa process efficiently. Some of the well-known IT companies that typically sponsor H-1B visas include:\n\n1. **Microsoft**\n2. **Google**\n3. **Amazon**\n4. **Apple**\n5. **Facebook (Meta)**\n6. **IBM**\n7. **Intel**\n8. **Oracle**\n9. **Cisco**\n10. **Salesforce**\n\nThese companies have a history of sponsoring H-1B visas for qualified candidates. When considering these opportunities, it's important for candidates to have a robust r\u00e9sum\u00e9 that highlights their education and relevant work experience to stand out during the recruitment process. Additionally, candidates should keep an eye on the latest H-1B sponsorship policies and updates from these companies as they can change over time.",
